<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>BP-R1 BOBTAIL BRAKE PROPORTIONING RELAY VALVE AND LQ-5 BOBTAIL LIMITING VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s04012" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5170" date="03/31/1996">
        <title>BP-R1 BOBTAIL BRAKE PROPORTIONING RELAY VALVE AND LQ-5 BOBTAIL LIMITING VALVE</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9700</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9800</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>04WAM</ucode>
                <ucode>04WAL</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The brake proportioning system is available in two configurations with the BP-R1 Bobtail Brake
                        Proportioning Relay Valve or the LQ-5 Bobtail Proportioning Limiting Valve.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>BP-R1 BOBTAIL BRAKE PROPORTIONING RELAY VALVE</title>
                    <para>The brake proportioning system may be configured (Code 04WAM) with a rear axle BP-R1
                        proportioning valve (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0401201">Figure 1</hotlnk>) only, to alter the amount of brake pressure to the
                        rear axle brakes when the tractor is operating in a "bobtail" mode (no trailer).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0401201" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0401201" filename="../figg04/G0401201.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. Brake Proportioning System Configurations</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. EXHAUST</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. CONTROL PORT</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. SERVICE PORT</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. SUPPLY PORT</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. CONTROL PORT</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <para>The BP-R1 valve is used for the rear axle(s) (with Code 04WAL or 04WAM) and is a combination
                        of two individual valves in a single housing. The lower portion, or body, of the BP-R1 contains
                        a "standard" service brake relay valve, which functions as a relay station to speed up brake
                        application and release.
                    </para>
                    <para>The upper portion, or cover, houses a brake proportioning valve which reduces normal service
                        brake application pressure when the tractor is not towing a trailer (bobtailing).
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>LQ-5 BOBTAIL LIMITING VALVE</title>
                    <para>The brake proportioning system may be configured (Code 04WAL) with an LQ-5 limiting valve (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0401202">Figure 2</hotlnk>) on the front axle and a BP-R1 proportioning valve
                        for the rear axle(s). This configuration alters the amount of front and drive axle braking
                        forces on tractors when the trailer is disconnected and operating in "bobtail" mode.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0401202" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0401202" filename="../figg04/G0401202.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2. LQ-5 Limiting Valve</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. SUPPLY PORT</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. STAMPED LQ-5 REPLACEMENT NO.</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. DELIVERY PORT</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CONTROL PORT</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                    <para>The LQ-5 valve is used (with Code 04WAL) on the front axle (steering axle) of tractor air
                        brake systems to reduce initial brake application pressure during normal tractor-trailer
                        operation. In the "bobtail mode" full air pressure is delivered to the brake chambers. The LQ-5
                        is designed for tractor systems only and replaces the front axle limiting valve. It is not used
                        on straight trucks or towing trucks. A quick release valve (QRV) (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0401203">Figure 3</hotlnk>) must be used between the LQ-5 delivery and the
                        front brake chambers.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0401203" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0401203" filename="../figg04/G0401203.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3. System Diagrams</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. FRONT AXLE AIR CHAMBER</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. TRAILER AIR SUPPLY VALVE (MV2 OR MV3 VALVE)</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. STOP LIGHT SWITCH</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. TRACTOR PROTECTION VALVE (TPV)</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. REAR AXLE BRAKE CHAMBER (4X2 SHOWN)</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. BP-R1 BOBTAIL PROPORTIONING RELAY VALVE</callout1>
                            <callout1>7. SUPPLY-5/8 GREEN W/6X4 OR 1/2 GREEN W/4X2</callout1>
                            <callout1>8. SERVICE - 3/8 GREEN</callout1>
                            <callout1>9. CONTROL - 3/8 RED</callout1>
                            <callout1>10. TO PARKING BRAKE</callout1>
                            <callout1>11. BRAKE CONTROL VALVE (FOOT VALVE)</callout1>
                            <callout1>12. DELIVERY 1/2 ORANGE</callout1>
                            <callout1>13. LQ-5 BOBTAIL LIMITING VALVE (CODE 04WAL ONLY)</callout1>
                            <callout1>14. DELIVERY 1/2 ORANGE</callout1>
                            <callout1>15. QUICK RELEASE VALVE (QRV)</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
